Message.MsgText: EJB_ENV_LOAD_FAILURE=WHFW0004E: Error loading WebSphere Application Server Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) Classes
Message.Explanation: One or more required classes could not be loaded while initializing a Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) Handler.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WebSphere configuration so that the Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) classes can be loaded.

Message.MsgText: EJB_FOUND_IN_SYSTEM_CLASSPATH=WHFW0019W: EJB handler {0} was found in the jar {1} which is in the system classpath. This handler will not be used.
Message.Explanation: You must define Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) Handlers in application Enterprise Archive (EAR) files.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the EJB Handler from the Java Archive (JAR) file or remove the jar from the system class path.

Message.MsgText: BEAN_PROPERTY_NOTFOUND=WHFW0011W: JavaBean property: {0} not found while setting the bean parameters during initialization of the System JavaBean Handler {1}.
Message.Explanation: System JavaBeans must include the specified property, which is missing.
Message.UserResponse: Add the missing property to the system JavaBean.

Message.MsgText: HANDLER_CONFIG_LOAD_FAILURE=WHFW0002E: Error loading Handler Configuration from Application {0}, module {1} and jar/module path {2}.
Message.Explanation: An error occurred while loading the Handler config from a Java 2 Platform, Enterprise Edition (J2EE) module.
Message.UserResponse: Provide the correct J2EE application, module name, and Java archive (JAR) path.

Message.MsgText: HANDLER_INIT_FAILURE=WHFW0008E: Error initializing Handler: {0} in Application: {1} and module {2}
Message.Explanation: An exception was encountered while initializing an Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) Handler.
Message.UserResponse: Check the FFDC logs for more information.

Message.MsgText: HANDLER_STOP_EVENT=WHFW0007I: Stop event for Handler: {0} in Application: {1} and Module: {2}
Message.Explanation: An application, which contains the Handler, has stopped.

Message.MsgText: HANDLER_START_EVENT=WHFW0006I: Start event for Handler: {0} in Application: {1} and Module: {2}
Message.Explanation: An application, which contains the Handler, has started.

Message.MsgText: NAMING_CONTEXT_FAILURE=WHFW0018E: Unable to create naming context for the service: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception was encountered while creating the specified WebSphere service.
Message.UserResponse: Check the FFDC logs for more information.

Message.MsgText: NO_JAVABEAN_PROPERTIES=WHFW0010W: No JavaBean properties found for the Handler: {0} during initialization of the System JavaBean Handler.
Message.Explanation: System JavaBeans must include the appropriate properties in order to be used as a Handler.
Message.UserResponse: Add the required properties to the system JavaBean.

Message.MsgText: SERVICE_LOOKUP_FAILURE=WHFW0015E: Failed to lookup: {0} service in JNDI.
Message.Explanation: The specified WebSphere service was not found, and is required.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WebSphere configuration to include the required service.

Message.MsgText: JAVABEAN_PARAMS_INIT_ERROR=WHFW0013E: Error initializing the JavaBean Handler: {0}.
Message.Explanation: An exception was encountered while loading and initializing a system JavaBean Handler.
Message.UserResponse: Check the FFDC logs for more information.

Message.MsgText: SERVICE_BIND_FAILURE=WHFW0017E: Failed to bind service: {0} to JNDI.
Message.Explanation: An exception was encountered while binding the specified WebSphere service to JNDI.
Message.UserResponse: Check the FFDC logs for more information.

Message.Explanation: The product supports system JavaBean and application Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) Handlers only.
Message.UserResponse: Use one of the supported Handler types in the Handler configuration.
